  "elapsed_s": 283.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so I rustled up a couple of my peers and began to try to see what we could do for these unfortunate people who were simply dropped on Star Street.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the only immediate roof that I could think of was, of course, the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I had terrible difficulty in attempting to get to the authorities that be to open the synagogue and to let us bring these people under the roof, to the point where eventually, we just had to break down the doors.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then we had considerable difficulty with the reluctance of the people to desecrate the, the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And of course, you also had difficulty with men and women being accommodated under the same roof and how you separate them, and then attempting to try to provide some means of, of hygiene.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You know, there were outhouses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But they certainly weren't prepared for that kind of a, of a massive number of people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, and then the, the question of feeding them arose.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And remember, this was Pesach.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the problems we have had because, essentially, the gendarmerie, which seems to have been almost exclusively in charge of the operation, weren't very kindly disposed on the one hand.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And on the other hand, the Jews of the city, being completely bewildered and lost, on the one hand, were afraid to have contact with the people who were brought in lest it have a deleterious impact on their existence.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were still in their homes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And as far as they were concerned, perhaps this transport of people that were brought in were brought in from the neighbor-- from the, the villagers because eventually, that-- those areas were going to become part of the, of the front line.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And maybe Jews were considered unreliable.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
